HEADWORD: Hydrant
<hw>Hy"drant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to irrigate,
fr. <grk>"y`dwr</grk> water. See <er>Hydra</er>.]</ety> <def>A discharge
pipe with a valve and spout at which water may be drawn from the mains
of waterworks; a water plug.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

